fields.description:
SVN repositories show up in quicksearch as:
{quote}
'The following repositories are still indexing, and might therefore deliver incomplete results'
{quote}
even if when indexing is complete.

!http://i.imgur.com/ZvKvm0U.png?2!

In the JIRA admin interface, if you upgrade the application Link to FishEye (because JIRA or FishEye has been upgraded for instance), then the config.xml is updated from <proxy-info/> to <proxy-info proxy-host="" proxy-scheme=""/> and this in turns causes the following situation if then trying to access the admin console of FishEye:

{noformat}
The requested resource cannot be found.
There is no Action mapped for namespace /admin/:/admin and action name login-default. Check if there is such an action name with such namespace defined in the xwork.xml and also if such an action class exists. Check also the log to see if the action class is successfully loaded.
{noformat}

From https://answers.atlassian.com/questions/200694/feature-request-filter-closed-hg-branches-in-drop-down
{quote}
The branches drop down when switching branches in the repository view in Fisheye or selecting changesets in Crucible only shows the first fifty branches alphabetically.

Once you start typing, you can filter on any branch which is good, but it would be of more value if the branches listed were only the active ones. Right now we don't see most of our active branches in the drop down because there are lots of closed branches from a couple of years ago that start with the letter A or B, making the drop down pretty useless for us.
{quote}

If the IP address of the FishEye server is not being allowed to connect to the JIRA User server (address that is not whitelisted), then the error message should be specific to this situation instead of having the generic JIRA source tab error:

{noformat}
Request to https://fisheye.hostname.com/ failed: Error in remote call to 'Fisheye CM' (https://fisheye.hostname.com) [AbstractRestCommand{path='/rest-service-fe/search-v1/crossRepositoryQuery', params=
{query=CM-3060, expand=changesets[0:20].revisions[0:29],reviews}
, methodType=GET}] : java.net.SocketTimeoutException: Read timed out
{noformat}

Even if you setup git with 32bit path like "d:\progra~1\git\cmd" on administration UI, Fisheye shows errors trying to use the 64bit path:
{noformat}
2013-07-26 07:07:45,696 INFO  [InitialPinger2 MC4-Basics] fisheye LoggingProcessMonitor-onAfterFinished - Exception executing command "E:\PROGRA~1\Git\cmd\git.exe clone --bare -v git@wcgitmaster.intellig.local:basics clone " Non-zero exit code: 128
com.atlassian.utils.process.ProcessException: Non-zero exit code: 128
{noformat}

Also there are some errors when the plugins are loading:
{noformat}
Skipping E:\Program Files (x86)\Atlassian\Crucible\bin\..\data\plugins\data: not found.
{noformat}

Moving FishEye to another folder like "d:\applications" solved the issue.

Steps to reproduce (while following [FishEye SSL Configuration|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/FISHEYE/FishEye+SSL+configuration]):
# Shutdown FishEye/Crucible.
# Generate a self-signed certificate with:
{noformat}
$JAVA_HOME/bin/keytool -keystore /path/to/keystore.kst -alias fisheye -genkey -keyalg RSA
{noformat}
or (using the default keystore):
{noformat}
$JAVA_HOME/bin/keytool -keystore /Users/user/.keystore -alias fisheye -genkey -keyalg RSA
{noformat}
# Edit the {{config.xml}} file adding the following:
{code:xml}
<web-server context="/"
  site-url="http://localhost:8060/">
<http bind=":8060"/>
<ssl bind=":8443" keystore="/path/to/keystore.kst" keystore-password="password123"/>
</web-server>
{code}
# Start FishEye/Crucible.
# Result:
{noformat}
2013-07-23 15:24:57,024 ERROR - Could not create webserver: null
{noformat}

Adding the truststore information resolves the issue, however the documentation states:
{quote}
| SSL Truststore | Optional setting. Path to the truststore file. May be the same as the keystore. Truststore is a list of trusted CAs. Format is the same as the keystore entry. | | 
| SSL Truststore Password | Optional setting. The password you used in the above step when creating the truststore file. If you did not set a password, leave this empty. See the passwords section | |
{quote}
